<subSubSection id="C34B6535FF83FFBB06C444E2FEB771BD" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF83FFBB06C444E2FDC77387" blockId="36.[164,779,952,1279]" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">
Previously 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB074D44E2FD077493" box="[301,743,982,1003]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB074D44E2FD037493" authorityName="Tschudi" authorityYear="1844" box="[301,739,982,1003]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Caprimulgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="longirostris" subSpecies="decussatus">Caprimulgus longirostris decussatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
It is elevated to full species status. Its phylogenetic position within 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB07364327FE007350" authorityName="Wagler" authorityYear="1832" box="[342,480,1043,1064]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB07364327FE007350" box="[342,480,1043,1064]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">Hydropsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not completely resolved in this study. It is part of a four-way polytomy that includes the following clades: (1) 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB04074365FCE4731D" baseAuthorityName="Tschudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[615,772,1104,1126]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="decussatus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB04074365FCE4731D" box="[615,772,1104,1126]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. decussatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (2) 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB06B04344FEC073FC" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[208,288,1135,1157]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyra">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB06B04344FEC073FC" box="[208,288,1135,1157]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. lyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB07074344FDEA73FD" baseAuthorityName="Cassin" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[359,522,1136,1157]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="segmentata">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB07074344FDEA73FD" box="[359,522,1136,1157]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. segmentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (3) 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB042A4344FD3273FC" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[586,722,1135,1157]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parvulus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB042A4344FD3273FC" box="[586,722,1135,1157]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. parvulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB06C443BAFED273DB" baseAuthorityName="Todd" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[164,306,1166,1187]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heterurus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB06C443BAFED273DB" box="[164,306,1166,1187]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. heterurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and (4) 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB07D543BAFD8373DB" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1825" box="[437,611,1166,1187]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Caprimulgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
H. 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB078143BAFD8373DB" box="[481,611,1166,1187]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB041A43BAFCE373DB" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[634,771,1166,1187]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="roraimae">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB041A43BAFCE373DB" box="[634,771,1166,1187]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. roraimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB06C44399FED173B9" baseAuthorityName="P. L. Sclater" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[164,305,1196,1218]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruficervix">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB06C44399FED173B9" box="[164,305,1196,1218]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. ruficervix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB07254399FE3773B9" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[325,471,1196,1218]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB07254399FE3773B9" box="[325,471,1196,1218]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB078A4399FD9E73B9" baseAuthorityName="Pelzeln" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[490,638,1196,1218]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="candicans">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB078A4399FD9E73B9" box="[490,638,1196,1218]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. candicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB04F24399FF157398" baseAuthorityName="Lawrence" baseAuthorityYear="1862" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculicaudus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB04F24399FF157398" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. maculicaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB076E43F8FE767398" baseAuthorityName="Nitzsch" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[270,406,1227,1249]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="forcipata">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB076E43F8FE767398" box="[270,406,1227,1249]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. forcipata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB07CF43F8FDA27398" baseAuthorityName="Lawrence" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[431,578,1227,1249]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albicauda">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB07CF43F8FDA27398" box="[431,578,1227,1249]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. albicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB043B43F8FCE37398" baseAuthorityName="J. F. Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[603,771,1227,1249]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cayennensis">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB043B43F8FCE37398" box="[603,771,1227,1249]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. cayennensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB06C443DEFEB67386" baseAuthorityName="Tschudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[164,342,1257,1279]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="climacocerca">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB06C443DEFEB67386" box="[164,342,1257,1279]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. climacocerca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB07FC43DEFDC77387" box="[412,551,1258,1279]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB07FC43DEFDC37387" baseAuthorityName="J. F. Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[412,547,1258,1279]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="torquata">H. torquata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF83FFBB06C44210FEF47241" blockId="36.[164,779,1316,1491]" box="[164,276,1316,1337]" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB06C44210FEF47241" box="[164,276,1316,1337]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF83FFBB06C44276FEAC72AB" blockId="36.[164,779,1316,1491]" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">
Small, cryptically coloured nightjar with a slender long bill. It is morphologically similar to 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB04B94256FEDE72ED" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. l. atripunctatus</emphasis>
in plumage and body shape, but much smaller in size. Territorial calls are also different (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC04B4FFF83FFBB06CB4289FEA172AB" author="Cleere N" box="[171,321,1469,1491]" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" refId="ref27056" refString="Cleere N. 2010. Nightjars, potoos, frogmouths, oilbirds and owlet-nightjars of the world. Old Basing, UK: WILDGuides Ltd., Parr House." type="book" year="2010">Cleere, 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF83FFBB06C442C3FEFB7174" blockId="36.[164,779,1527,1733]" box="[164,283,1527,1548]" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB06C442C3FEFB7174" box="[164,283,1527,1548]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF83FFBB06C44122FEB771BD" blockId="36.[164,779,1527,1733]" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">
Genetic evidence strongly supports 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB040E4122FCEB7153" baseAuthorityName="Tschudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[622,779,1558,1579]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Hydropsalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="decussatus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB040E4122FCEB7153" box="[622,779,1558,1579]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. decussatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being an independent diagnosable species (
<figureCitation id="136A2A3BFF83FFBB04DB4100FD1D7132" box="[699,765,1588,1610]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="21.[144,223,1811,1830]" captionTargetBox="[222,838,194,1777]" captionTargetId="graphics-2@21.[176,809,162,1777]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 7. A phylogeny of the Hydropsalis group of the South American clade based on a maximum-likelihood (ML) analysis of a concatenated 5298-bp molecular data set. ML bootstrap values higher than 60 and Bayesian posterior probability values higher than 0.95 are displayed on the nodes. Names on the tree represent current taxonomy; names on the right represent those resulting from this revision (see text)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5346446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5346446/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Although formerly a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB04234167FEC671FE" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1825" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Caprimulgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris" subGenus="Caprimulgus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB04234167FDBF7110" box="[579,607,1619,1640]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB040D4167FCE27110" box="[621,770,1619,1640]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">Caprimulgus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB06C44145FEC671FE" box="[164,294,1649,1670]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the phylogenetic results show that it is distant from 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF83FFBB075841A5FE3C71DD" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1825" box="[312,476,1680,1702]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Caprimulgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF83FFBB075841A5FE3C71DD" box="[312,476,1680,1702]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="542">H. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, despite some morphological similarities.
</paragraph>
